-- Telkom CEO ‘Not Hopeful’ of KT Corp Deal, Business Day Reports
-- B y   H i l t o n   S h o n e
-- 2012-06-04T05:15:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-04/telkom-ceo-not-hopeful-of-kt-corp-deal-business-day-reports.html
Telkom SA Ltd. (TKG)  is “not hopeful” the
South African government will reverse a decision not to support
the sale of a 20 percent stake to  KT Corp. (030200) , Business Day
reported, citing Chief Executive Officer Nombulelo Moholi.  Africa’s largest fixed-line phone company will “engage”
with the government to clarify its decision, the Johannesburg-
based newspaper said, citing Moholi.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Hilton Shone at 
 hshone@bloomberg.net  